Seg 1 - Play.java lines - Lines 1-60

- I did have to research how to use an enumeration but the code is
all done by myself. I picked this one because we had to deliberate
and spent a solid amount of time determining which plays are good/bad
against other plays and had to hard code those in.


Seg 2 - PlayerPool.java - Lines 1-60

- Nothing extravagant or very technical but we did want to make this a fantasy
style game and you cant have that without real people. It took me some time but
i found 30 players from this years Tampa Bay open and made up stats for all of them.


Seg 3 - PLayer.java - lines 1-55

- Basic abstract class that defines stats and has teh required getters and setters.

==============================

= = = Marcus = = =

Seg 1 - Team.java -  lines - 1-124

- I chose this class because it is the base for all teams in the game and stores shared
data like roster, points, wins, and eliminations while using abstraction and Comparable so
teams can have unique behaviors and be sorted by points for standings.

Seg 2 - MatchEngine.java - Lines 1-120
- I chose this class because it runs the main match simulation, including rounds, player
duels, eliminations, and deciding both round and match winners. The most challenging part
was balancing the combat system using player stats, randomness, and play multipliers so
outcomes felt fair but still unpredictable.

Seg 3 - FrontPlayer.java - Line 1-22
- I chose this class because it defines the FrontPlayer role and overrides the overall rating
so agility is weighted more heavily than gun skill (60/40 split), which matches how front players
rely more on movement and positioning.


============================================
===             Sorting                  ===
============================================

We implemented sorting in this program with:

1: Sorting the Standings by points.

- After all preliminary matches have been played the ranking from 1-4 is sorted
based on how many points were accumulated. This is important because it determines
who the top 2 teams are and who moves on to the championship. This is done using
bubble sort in the tournament class:

for (int i = 0; i < standings.length - 1; i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < standings.length - 1 - i; j++) {
        if (standings[j].getPoints() < standings[j + 1].getPoints()) {
            Team temp = standings[j];
            standings[j] = standings[j + 1];
            standings[j + 1] = temp;
        }
    }
}
